headline: November jobs report, retail sales, Lennar earnings: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come tomorrow, Tuesday, December 16, including the release of the November jobs report, retail sales data, and earnings results from homebuilder Lennar (LEN). To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Is Lennar Attractively Priced After Recent Share Price Pullback?
summary: If you are wondering whether Lennar is finally trading at a price that makes sense for long term investors, or if the market is still misreading the housing cycle, this article will walk you through what the numbers are really saying about its valuation. Despite a solid 50.2% gain over three years and 75.1% over five, Lennar is down 10.9% year to date and 13.3% over the last year, suggesting sentiment has cooled even as the long term trend remains positive.
